e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fund companies are rebranding their out-of-f=
ashion investment offerings as green, hoping to grab a portion of the cash =
pouring into sustainable products. In some cases, the rebranding has been i=
n name only.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last year, companies that mana=
ge mutual funds and exchange-traded funds rebranded a record 25 funds as su=
stainable, according to Morningstar. They say these funds have adopted inve=
stment strategies that utilize data on companies=E2=80=99 environmental, so=
cial and governance performance to pick stocks. Since 2013, fund companies =
have rebranded 64 funds, which had $35 billion in assets as of June. =E2=80=
=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Many of these funds are actively manage=
d and were experiencing chronic outflows prior to rebranding, said Mornings=
tar Head of Sustainability Research Jon Hale. =E2=80=9CYou have big fund co=
mpanies with an inventory of funds, a lot of which aren=E2=80=99t really at=
tracting assets anymore, saying =E2=80=98OK, here=E2=80=99s this new invest=
ment trend happening; what do we do?=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D Mr. Hale said.</p></=
blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the one hand, =E2=80=9Cthere is =
probably a lot of value to be created by <em>telling people soothing things=
 about ESG</em>, and in practice, if someone creates that value, a lot of i=
ntermediaries in the chain will capture some of it.=E2=80=9D Putting the wo=
rd =E2=80=9CSustainable=E2=80=9D in the name of a mutual fund,=C2=A0<em>and=
 doing nothing else</em>, clearly=C2=A0<em>creates value:=C2=A0</em>It make=
s people who buy the fund slightly happier than they would otherwise be.=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, why not? There are p=
eople whose job is basically =E2=80=9Cpick companies that are good and buy =
their stocks.=E2=80=9D This used to be a big popular job, and mutual fund c=
ompanies employed lots of those people. Now, in the traditional form =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cpick companies whose stocks will go up=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0it is a bit disfavored; people like passive investing (or YOLOing Gam=
eStop calls), not active mutual funds. But there is a close-enough variant,=
 =E2=80=9Cpick companies that are good citizens of the world and buy their =
stocks.=E2=80=9D Why shouldn=E2=80=99t active managers retool and become=C2=
=A0sustainable managers?</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=
=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
